summary: skam france is really hitting me straight in the feels from every angle holy shit. all the little changes that they made...
body: skam france is really hitting me straight in the feels from every angle holy shit. all the little changes that they made regarding the topic of sexuality aka the main and most important topic of the season??  alexia becoming a sort of gay guru herself, all the mentions to her bisexuality, the calling out of basile’s problematic behaviour by daphné, eliott straight up telling lucas he could end up with a boy… I could go on and on, I think it is so important that they decided to go all in and really go full gay because there are soooo many stuff regarding sexuality that need to be discussed and what better way to do it than in a season centering around a boy questioning his own?? And ofc I am not only amazed by the contents but also by the delivery….I don’t think i can coherently put into words how i felt watching this week and last week’s friday clips because as i watched them all i could do was scream into my pillow just from how fucking good they were. the chemistry between lucas and eliott is so so so on point, I don’t even know how they do it!!! this season manages to struck some chords in me just like the og s3 did and I am feeling stuff i hadn’t felt watching any other remake until now and i am just so fucking grateful for how well it all is coming together, I really have no words.

summary: One thing I love about Skam France over Skam OG (never thought I’d say that who am it?) is that S3 of Skam OG was only from Isak...
body:
One thing I love about Skam France over Skam OG (never thought I’d say that who am it?) is that S3 of Skam OG was only from Isak POV exclusively. One effect it had was that we were never quite sure what Even’s feelings were. Of course we had moments but for the first ¾ of the season, we weren’t sure if Even liked Isak as much or if he was just being a fuck boi or what was up. That worked for Skam OG because the whole mystery of what was up with Even was part of Isak’s journey. 

What I love about Skam France is that we are not just getting Lucas’ POV, we are seeing Eliott’s POV too. It started with the trailer and we continue to get small glimpses.  Like watching Eliott watching Lucas play piano (still not over it) and tonight when we got to see Eliott watching Lucas kiss Chloe. I love that. We get to see that Eliott is falling just as hard for Lucas, there is no mystery. It’s all there for us to see.

I’m loving these small changes, it’s really making Skam France it’s own thing.
